SIMPLE: etiolation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Etiolation
<hw>E`ti*o*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
operation of blanching plants, by excluding the light of the sun; the
condition of a blanched plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Paleness produced by absence of
light, or by disease.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etiolin</ent>⟦br⟧
